{
  "texts": [
    "They generate a vector field X D ∈ Γ(T M).",
    "Computing fibrewise in a local trivialisation as in [Lau11, p. 3] we deduce the claimed formula for the Lie derivative (we notice that there is a sign error in the formula from [Lau11], which does not affect the results of that paper whatsoever).",
    "□ Remark 3.3.",
    "When N ≃ R d is abelian, conditions (ii) and (iii) in Ansatz 3.1 reduce to the minimality of the orbits and the fact that, on a trivialisation U × R d adapted to the flat connection H, the soliton vector field is half the Euler vector field x i ∂ ∂x i on R d. This is precisely the Ansatz used by Lott in [Lot07, §4].",
    "The next result shows that, under Ansatz 3.1, the expanding Ricci soliton equation (1) reduces to the twisted harmonic-Einstein equations (4).Proposition 3.4."
  ]
}